organic_results.snippet: Carla O'Connor University of Michigan~ j ho fails and who succeeds in America's schools? For sociologists of education, the significance of this question rests with the fact that academic performance is socially stratified. Some social groups repeatedly outstrip the academic performance of others. But while sociologists of education have become reasonably adept at identifying group and even subgroup differences in educational achievement, we still struggle to explain why and how these differences emerge.
